Active candidates are those whose campaign status is 'active'; 
The sentiment score is a measure of the sentiment of a statement, with higher scores indicating more positive sentiments; 
The overall average sentiment score is the average sentiment score of all statements made by a candidate on a particular topic; 
The total sentiment count is the total number of statements made by a candidate on a particular topic.

This query seems to be used in a political context to analyze the performance and popularity of candidates based on their statements and campaign contributions.

Total contributions refer to the sum of all campaign contributions a candidate received for a specific statement; 
Access count represents the number of times a candidate's statement was accessed.
